<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911101-0061</DOCNO><DOCID>911101-0061.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Hoogovens en Staalfabrieken:   Dutch Firm to Post Loss   For '91 Due to Revamping</HL><DATE>11/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11</SO><CO>   N.NEH</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)</IN><RE>EUROPE (EU)NETHERLANDS (NL)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Hoogovens en Staalfabrieken N.V., the Dutch steel andaluminum maker, said it will probably post a loss for 1991.   Although Hoogovens said that it will post &quot;only a verymodest profit on its ordinary activities for the full year,&quot;the company said restructuring charges for its Belgianaluminum operations will cost the company &quot;several tens ofmillions of guilders.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   As a result, the company, based in Ijmuiden, theNetherlands, said that it will fall into the red in 1991.   The warning represents a significant lowering of the Dutchsteel and aluminum company's expectations. As recently asAugust, Hoogovens said that it would likely break even in thesecond half of 1991 after posting a net profit of 55 millionguilders ($29 million) the first half.</TEXT></DOC>